<!--
  Wazuh Browser Privacy Monitor — Decoder
  Author  : Ram Kumar G (IT Fortress)
  Version : 2.0.2 (Phase 3 - Privacy-Safe Telemetry Edition)

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  WHY THE PRIMARY PATH NEEDS NO CUSTOM DECODER
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Installers configure the agent with:
        <localfile>
          <log_format>json</log_format>
          <location>.../browser_privacy.log</location>
        </localfile>

    For log_format=json, Wazuh's native JSON decoder runs and sets
    decoder.name="json". Custom <prematch> decoders only run in the
    text/syslog pipeline and are NEVER applied to JSON localfiles.
    Therefore the rules (0320-browser_privacy_rules.xml) use:
        <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
        <field name="integration">browser-privacy-monitor</field>
    which is the documented Wazuh pattern (same as VirusTotal).

    This decoder file is only used for PATH B — syslog relay — where
    the collector's JSON log is forwarded via rsyslog / syslog-ng.

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  FIX HISTORY
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    v1.x — BROKEN
        Used <prematch>{"integration": "browser-privacy-monitor"</prematch>.
        The leading '{' is interpreted as an OSSEC regex quantifier
        and analysisd aborts with:
          ERROR: (1452): Syntax error on regex: '^\{'
          ERROR: (2107): Decoder configuration error
          CRITICAL: (1202): Configuration error at ...

    v2.0.0 — Removed the broken prematch entirely. Two top-level
        <decoder> siblings (correct format). Verified by inspecting
        official Wazuh ruleset decoders (e.g. 0310-ssh_decoders.xml
        has 24 top-level <decoder> elements, no wrapper).

    v2.0.1 — WRONG FIX (reverted). Added a <decoders> wrapper based
        on a mistaken assumption about the Manager API validator.
        analysisd then rejects the file with:
          ERROR: (1230): Invalid element in the configuration: 'decoders'
          CRITICAL: (1202): Configuration error at ...

    v2.0.2 — CURRENT. Back to the correct Wazuh format: multiple
        <decoder> entries at the top level, NO wrapper. This form
        loads cleanly in analysisd and is the same layout used by
        every built-in Wazuh decoder file.

        If the Wazuh Dashboard editor still shows a validation error
        when saving this file, check:
          1. File perms: chown wazuh:wazuh, chmod 660
          2. No BOM / no Windows CRLF line endings
          3. No unescaped special chars added by the editor

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  PATH B — log_format="syslog" (syslog relay / forwarded)

  Example syslog line:
    Apr 18 10:00:00 WIN-01 browser-privacy-monitor: {"integration":...

  Forwarding-host localfile:
    <localfile>
      <log_format>syslog</log_format>
      <location>/var/log/browser-privacy-monitor.log</location>
    </localfile>
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-->

<decoder name="browser-privacy-monitor-syslog">
  <program_name>^browser-privacy-monitor$</program_name>
</decoder>

<decoder name="browser-privacy-monitor-syslog-json">
  <parent>browser-privacy-monitor-syslog</parent>
  <plugin_decoder>JSON_Decoder</plugin_decoder>
</decoder>
